🔹 1. What is Git vs GitHub?

Git = Version control system (tracks changes in your code locally)

GitHub = Website to store and collaborate on Git repositories online

Think of it like:

Git = engine

GitHub = cloud storage + collaboration platform

🟢 BEGINNER LEVEL
✅ Step 1: Install Git

Download from:
👉 https://git-scm.com

Check installation:

git --version

✅ Step 2: Configure Git (First Time Only)
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"

✅ Step 3: Create a Local Repository
mkdir myproject
cd myproject
git init


Now Git is tracking your folder.

✅ Step 4: Add and Commit Files

Create a file (example: index.html)

Check status:

git status


Add file:

git add index.html


Or add all files:

git add .


Commit:

git commit -m "First commit"

🟢 Connect to GitHub
✅ Step 5: Create Repository on GitHub

Go to GitHub

Click New Repository

Create repo (without README if already local)

✅ Step 6: Connect Local Repo to GitHub

Copy the repo URL and run:

git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo-name.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main


Now your code is on GitHub 🎉

